XVII.

STILL to be neat, still to be drest, As you were going to a feast3

Still to be powdered, still persumed:

Lady‚ it is to be presumed, Though art’s hid causes are not found, All is not sweet, all is not sound.

Give me a look, give me a face That makes simplicity a grace ; Robes loosely flowing, hair as free ; Such sweet neglect more taketh me Than all the adulteries of art-

They strike mine eye, but not my heart.

BEN JONSON. -
